### Annotations Basics

Annotations (metadata) start with `@` and provide additional information about code elements.

```dart
@Deprecated('Use newMethod instead')
void oldMethod() {
  // ...
}

@override
void someMethod() {
  // ...
}

void main() {
  oldMethod(); // Shows deprecation warning
}
```

### Built-in Annotations

| Annotation | Purpose |
|------------|---------|
| `@override` | Indicates method override |
| `@Deprecated('message')` | Marks as deprecated with message |
| `@deprecated` | Marks as deprecated (no message) |
| `@pragma('...')` | Compiler directives |
| `@immutable` | Class should be immutable |
| `@required` | (Dart 2) Named param required |

### Custom Annotations

```dart
class Todo {
  final String who;
  final String what;
  final DateTime when;

  const Todo(this.who, this.what, this.when);
}

@Todo('Alice', 'Implement error handling', DateTime(2025, 12, 31))
void processData() {
  // TODO: Implement
}

void main() {
  // Annotations can be retrieved at runtime
}
```

### Retrieving Annotations with Reflection

```dart
import 'dart:mirrors';

class Important {
  final String reason;
  const Important(this.reason);
}

@Important('Core business logic')
class BusinessRule {
  void execute() {}
}

void main() {
  // Using dart:mirrors (not available in Flutter)
  // In Flutter, use code generation instead
  print('Annotations can be read with dart:mirrors');
}
```

### Annotation Targets

```dart
// Annotations can be applied to:
@Deprecated('Use X')
class MyClass {}

@Deprecated('Use Y')
typedef MyFunction = void Function();

@Deprecated('Use Z')
void myFunction() {}

@Deprecated('Use W')
int myField = 0;

// Target-specific
class Target {
  @Deprecated('Use other')
  final int value;

  const Target(this.value);
}
```

### Pragma Annotations

```dart
void main() {
  // Common pragma directives
  @pragma('vm:entry-point')
  void entryPoint() {}

  // Inline/inlining control
  @pragma('vm:prefer-inline')
  int smallFunction() => 42;
}
```

> **Key Point:** Use `@override` and `@Deprecated` frequently. For custom metadata in Flutter, prefer code generation (json_serializable, freezed) over runtime reflection since `dart:mirrors` is not available in Flutter.

codeExample:
class Author {
  final String name;
  final String email;
  const Author(this.name, this.email);
}

class Version {
  final String version;
  final String date;
  const Version(this.version, this.date);
}

@Author('Alice Johnson', 'alice@example.com')
@Version('2.0.0', '2026-01-15')
class ApiService {
  @Deprecated('Use fetchUsers instead')
  void getUsers() {
    // Old implementation
  }

  void fetchUsers() {
    print('Fetching users...');
  }
}

void main() {
  var api = ApiService();
  api.fetchUsers();
}
